article.headline: Sacramento State 72, Montana State 52
article.story: BOZEMAN (AP) -- Jason Erickson scored 28 points Friday to lead Montana State to a 79-73 exhibition victory over MBC Nikolaev, a team from Ukraine. The Bobcats built their largest lead, 76-53, on two free throws by Erickson with 3:28 to play. MBC Nikolaev went on a 20-3 run behind the 3-point shooting of Evgen Podorvannyy to make the final score close. Podorvannyy scored 18 of his 22 points in the final 4:49. Montana State jumped out to a 21-8 lead near the midway point of the first half and eventually stretched the lead to 33-18 on a layup by Erickson with three minutes left in the half. But the Ukranians made a run in the closing minutes, using a 10-1 spurt to pull within 34-28 at halftime. Calvin Ento and Nick Dissly each added 10 points for Montana State.
